# Build-context hygiene + secret exclusion (W7-WR-01).
# The Dockerfile COPYs only requirements.txt, src/, and .actor/ — so the
# security-critical lines below are the .actor/ credential files (a dev-placed
# .actor/input.json would otherwise be baked into a persistent image layer by
# `COPY .actor/ ./.actor/`). The rest just shrink the context sent to `apify push`.

# ── Secrets / local inputs — NEVER bake into the image ──
.env
.env.*
input.json
.actor/input.json
.actor/storage/
cookies.json
*_state.json
*state.json
last_run.json
*.pem
*.key
*service*account*.json
*-key.json

# ── Version control + planning (local-only) ──
.git/
.gitignore
.planning/

# ── Local outputs / logs / data ──
output/
logs/
data/

# ── Python caches / virtualenvs ──
__pycache__/
**/__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.venv/
venv/

# ── Dev-only material not needed in the Actor image ──
tests/
scripts/
docs/
assets/
templates/
Skills for REI/
*.md
